<subSubSection id="C37E21C1BC1CFFF6FF4FF9D1FB83FE05" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1453" pageId="2" pageNumber="1452" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDB724ABC1CFFF7FF4FF9D1FE20F98C" blockId="2.[160,1155,1598,1727]" box="[160,394,1598,1623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1452">
<emphasis id="B910AE58BC1CFFF7FF4FF9D1FE20F98C" bold="true" box="[160,394,1598,1623]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1452">Amended diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDB724ABC1CFFF6FF4FF98DFB83FE05" blockId="2.[160,1155,1598,1727]" lastBlockId="3.[160,1156,142,478]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="1453" pageId="2" pageNumber="1452">
Cave-dwelling harvestmenı scutum zeta 
<typeStatus id="54DFCCE8BC1CFFF7FD85F98DFD31F9A1" box="[618,667,1634,1658]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1452">type</typeStatus>
(ζ) but with prominent rounded and clear projections on opisthosomal tergite 1ı similar projections are present on posterior corners of scutum and free tergites. Area of lateral channels very highı occupying a large portion in lateral view. Ocularium inconspicuous in the middle of prosoma. Dorsal ornamentation variableı from rugose to tuberculate (
<figureCitation id="135F6ECFBC1DFFF6FDD5FF5EFD3EFF12" box="[570,660,177,201]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1624,1647]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1592]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[163,1153,142,1592]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Habitus of Huasteca species. (a) male of Huasteca gratiosa. (b) male of Huasteca rugosa. (c) female of Huasteca silhavyi. (d) female of Huasteca kardia sp. nov. Scale bars = 0.5 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3670141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1453">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). Cheliceral-fixed finger with cheliceral comb (
<figureCitation id="135F6ECFBC1DFFF6FF48FF3BFEAFFF37" box="[167,261,212,236]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1458,1481]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1426]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[163,1153,142,1426]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Chelicera and pedipalp of Huasteca kardia sp. nov. (a) chelicera frontal, male. (b) chelicera mesal, male. (c) cheliceral comb, male. (d) chelicera ectal, male. (e) pedipalp mesal. Scale bars = a and b: 150 µm, c: 50 µm, d and e: 250 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670145" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3670145/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1453">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(c)). Apical portion of femur II in males slightly swollenı sometimes patella and basal portion of tibia II also swollen (
<figureCitation id="135F6ECFBC1DFFF6FDACFF19FD35FED5" box="[579,671,246,270]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1380,1403]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1349]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[163,1153,142,1349]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 2. Habitus and venter of Huasteca kardia sp. nov. (a) habitus holotype. (b) habitus female paratype. (c) venter holotype. (d) venter female paratype. Dotted line indicates swollen portions of leg II. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3670143/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1453">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). Stigmatic area shortı T-shapedı narrow in males. Pars distalis of penis compressedı with a thin flimsy laminaı asymmetrical in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6409C9BC1DFFF6FF4FFED4FEA5FE8F" authorityName="Cruz-Lopez and Franckei" authorityYear="2015" box="[160,271,315,340]" class="Arachnida" family="Stygnopsidae" genus="Huasteca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Opiliones" pageId="3" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silhavyi">
<emphasis id="B910AE58BC1DFFF6FF4FFED4FEA5FE8F" box="[160,271,315,340]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1453">H. silhavyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two pairs of both macrosetae C and A forming a row on lateral margin of pars distalisı two or three pairs of macrosetae D on the base of follis and presence of both small macrosetae E1 and E2 on ventro-apical portion of flimsy lamina plus one additional more basally placed macrosetae E. Follis almost twice as long as wideı with two-lobed lateral projections (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF50FBBBC1DFFF6FE9CFE29FD16FE05" author="Cruz-Lopez JAi Francke OF" box="[371,700,454,478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1453" pagination="827 - 891" refId="ref4368" refString="Cruz-Lopez JAi Francke OF. 2015. Cladistic analysis and taxonomic revision of the genus Karos goodnight &amp; goodnighti 1944 (Opilionesi Laniatoresi Stygnopsidae). Zool J Linn Soc. 175: 827 - 891. doi: 10.1111 / zoj. 12299" type="journal article" year="2015">Cruz-López and Francke 2015</bibRefCitation>
: figures 47ı 50ı 53 and 
<figureCitation id="135F6ECFBC1DFFF6FC2DFE29FBB6FE05" box="[962,1052,454,478]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="9.[160,225,769,792]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,738]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[163,1153,142,738]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 5. Male genitalia of Huasteca kardia sp. nov. (a) dorsal. (b) lateral. (c) ventral. Macrosetae A-E indicated in the figures, adE = additional macrosetae E. Scale bars = 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3670149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3670149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1453">Figure 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
